    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for the discerning collector is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, showcasing the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This specimen features the iconic 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, maintaining exceptional compression and a perfectly synchronized sequential twin-turbocharger system. The powertrain is mated to a precise 5-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, preserving the legendary 50/50 weight distribution. The chassis remains taut with original double-wishbone suspension components and zero structural oxidation. Finished in its factory Montego Blue Mica with a flawless interior, this RX-7 is mechanically stock, avoiding the heat-soak issues common in modified examples. A rare opportunity to own a preserved rotary masterpiece with a pristine engine bay and documented service history.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Mint condition. Garage kept. Full service history. No accidents. Smoke-free interior. Inspections welcome.",
